commit_message:
Prevent binding IPv6 addresses to Neutron interfaces

Explicitly disable IPv6 on Neutron created interfaces in the default
namespace before setting link up. Since the default behavior of IPv6 is
to bind to all interfaces as opposed to IPv4 where an address must be
explicitly configured we disable IPv6 on each interface before enabling
the interface. This avoids leaving a time window between when the
interface is enabled and when it is attached to bridge device during
which the host could be access from a tenant network.

Move disable_ipv6() from BridgeDevice to base IPDevice class so it is
usable by all interfaces. Then we explicitly disable IPv6 on veth
interfaces in the default namespaces and VXLAN and VLAN interfaces
created by the LinuxBridge agent.

In addition vlan interface is moved from LinuxBridgeManager to IPWrapper
so it can return an IPDevice object.

Conflicts:
	neutron/agent/linux/bridge_lib.py

commit_message:
ovs_lib: Fix a race between get_port_tag_dict and port removal

get_port_tag_dict() gets a list of ports using get_port_name_list()
and then queries the db again for ports in the list.
It fails if some of ports disappeared in between.
This change fixes it by ignoring "not exist" errors in the later query.

Closes-Bug: #1444797
Change-Id: Ic54b644bb1d72a4664b70f124863d17805c26fff
(cherry picked from commit d36940b720616ec6607c62eca50023eb00bdae01)

commit_message:
Install apparmor b/c Docker.io has undeclared dep

Docker has an undeclared dependency on apparmor for Ubuntu Trusty,
preventing the daemon from running and causing any -src jobs for IPA to
fail when using docker to build the package.

This should unbreak the IPA gate.

This is not a direct cherry-pick, as ironic in Mitaka uses a devstack
plugin, while ironic in Liberty uses devstack directly. This is,
however, a direct port from ironic's master branch. The commit there is
3a6a8ec98e56816c4671648d11716d71adc366b0.

Change-Id: I4c19c96d2d5cd8accb9ed8df6241fc9f0c229e0e
Co-Authored-By: Jay Faulkner <jay@jvf.cc>

commit_message:
Move stable compat jobs up to mitaka

Once every project has a mitaka branch move the stable compat jobs up
from liberty to mitaka. Note do not merge this until every project has a
mitaka branch otherwise we will be testing against master which provides
no stable compat information.

Change-Id: I30ac575fd4f58f4c37950388b707c133bd4bf9ca

commit_message:
Disable tempest in networking-odl rally job.

Tempest is not needed in a rally job.  It now causes the job to fail as
both try to create a Nova flavor called "m1.nano".

Change-Id: I04f2ab7f24148433468983e83fd859adde519958
Signed-off-by: Russell Bryant <rbryant@redhat.com>

commit_message:
Swift busted with Heka

Swift and heka were broken by an optimization that resulted in
a regression in commit:
0a1486a2c73275009f7158c911e7bfd683e40a58

This patch fixes that problem.

Change-Id: I02c6cf4de4f807c3ec66e2d4f59f182d0b864ea3
Closes-Bug: #1560788
(cherry picked from commit 8307b06a46b77f8b57a65b2eb74d797e5b794ca6)

subject: move fedora23 devstack to experimental
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-03-23 16:20:17.000000000', 'files': ['zuul/layout.yaml'], 'message': 'move fedora23 devstack to experimental

fedora23 job is quite often taking the full 3 hours to timeout and
fail its tests on devstack, which is holding up getting changes
landed.

There are multiple contributing factors:

* fedora23 is on non performance nodes (reason unknown)
* as such it only has 4 cores, so tempest is only running 2 way
* there is no wheel cache, so 13 minutes are spent installing python packages
* rpm package installation runs nearly 8 minutes

Various of these should be addressed and get the timing under control
in experimental before we move it back to check.

Change-Id: I77bf276dd791e7efdc3ac99c5c3d31558f684223
'}]
commit_message:
move fedora23 devstack to experimental

fedora23 job is quite often taking the full 3 hours to timeout and
fail its tests on devstack, which is holding up getting changes
landed.

There are multiple contributing factors:

* fedora23 is on non performance nodes (reason unknown)
* as such it only has 4 cores, so tempest is only running 2 way
* there is no wheel cache, so 13 minutes are spent installing python packages
* rpm package installation runs nearly 8 minutes

Various of these should be addressed and get the timing under control
in experimental before we move it back to check.

Change-Id: I77bf276dd791e7efdc3ac99c5c3d31558f684223

revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2016-03-23 18:43:59.000000000', 'files': ['specs/newton/approved/resource-providers.rst'], 'message': 'Re-propose resource-providers for Newton

This blueprint partially addresses the problem of Nova assuming all
resources are provided by a single compute node by introducing a new
concept -- a resource provider -- that will allow Nova to accurately
track and reserve resources regardless of whether the resource is being
exposed by a single compute node, some shared resource pool or an
external resource-providing service of some sort.

The spec has been annotated to reflect which work has been completed and

Change-Id: Id0c030159fa741a5eb51d52332d6fdbce05000ae
Previously-approved: Mitaka

commit_message:
Re-propose resource-providers for Newton

This blueprint partially addresses the problem of Nova assuming all
resources are provided by a single compute node by introducing a new
concept -- a resource provider -- that will allow Nova to accurately
track and reserve resources regardless of whether the resource is being
exposed by a single compute node, some shared resource pool or an
external resource-providing service of some sort.

The spec has been annotated to reflect which work has been completed and
which remains to be done in Newton.

Change-Id: Id0c030159fa741a5eb51d52332d6fdbce05000ae
Previously-approved: Mitaka

subject: Fix check for cross-referring self-dependencies
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2016-03-23 10:58:03.000000000', 'files': ['nailgun/nailgun/test/unit/test_task_based_deployment.py', 'nailgun/nailgun/orchestrator/task_based_deployment.py'], 'message': 'Fix check for cross-referring self-dependencies

This fix fixes an issue when the code of cross-reference
checking was too strict and checked not combination of
"task_name", "node_id",
but
only "node_id" instead.
This leads to the situation when cross-depends role: .*
does not include the task on the same node even
when task names of the required and of the requiring
tasks are different.

E.g. such dependency:

with nodes [1,2]
task: a
cross-depends:
   name: b

on node_id 1

should have requires: (b,1), (b,2)

but had requires: (b,2)

due to this bug

Change-Id: Ic8b6f86533670fe477cc68db6a0d932ee8501cc3
Closes-bug: #1559968
'}]
commit_message:
Fix check for cross-referring self-dependencies

This fix fixes an issue when the code of cross-reference
checking was too strict and checked not combination of
"task_name", "node_id",
but
only "node_id" instead.
This leads to the situation when cross-depends role: .*
does not include the task on the same node even
when task names of the required and of the requiring
tasks are different.

E.g. such dependency:

with nodes [1,2]
task: a
cross-depends:
   name: b

on node_id 1

should have requires: (b,1), (b,2)

but had requires: (b,2)

due to this bug

Change-Id: Ic8b6f86533670fe477cc68db6a0d932ee8501cc3
Closes-bug: #1559968

commit_message:
Refactor out opensack::swift::* classes

We have tradtionally employed a combined storage and swift proxy role/task
but they are kept seperate in both our aged openstack::swift::* and in the
swift module its self.

In this review, we will refactor the single swift.pp task to separate proxy.pp
and storage.pp tasks. In these tasks, we are only altering what was previously
in swift.pp with the inclusion of the openstack::swift::* classes directly in
task. In order to minimise review burden, we will follow up with another
review to flatten out the openstack::swift::* calls

Change-Id: I1d5d6024a7491b0c58bbd65f958d2f61e797233c
Blueprint: fuel-remove-conflict-openstack

commit_message:
Fix SwiftPostObject options usage in SwiftService

SwiftService().post(cont, [SwiftPostObject(obj, options]) currently
ignores options['header'], raises exception when options['headers']
is set and make malformed metadata when options['meta'] is set.

Fix tipos in code, add unittest for SwiftService().post
Closes-Bug: #1560052

Change-Id: Ie460f753492e9b73836b4adfc7c9c0f2130a8a91

subject: Cache instance overhead
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2016-03-23 12:52:05.000000000', 'files': ['nova_powervm/virt/powervm/driver.py', 'nova_powervm/tests/virt/powervm/test_driver.py'], 'message': "Cache instance overhead

The inputs to calculate_memory_overhead_on_host are the host UUID, which
is always the same in a NovaLink environment, and a single max_mem value
gleaned from the instance's flavor.  As such, it is not necessary to
invoke the expensive QueryReservedMemoryRequiredForPartition Job every
time we see a given max_mem value.

With this change set, the driver caches the instance overhead value
associated with each max_mem value it sees, making subsequent lookup
against that value effectively instantaneous.

The motivation for this change is scale.  It takes about one second for
QueryReservedMemoryRequiredForPartition to come back.  Since the
estimate_instance_overhead API is invoked via a periodic task, once per
second, serially across all instances, the driver begins to choke once
we reach about 80 instances on the host.

Change-Id: I5650b21b486658921b454a7ac0cd8ab745604b57
Closes-Bug: 1560668
"}]
commit_message:
Cache instance overhead

The inputs to calculate_memory_overhead_on_host are the host UUID, which
is always the same in a NovaLink environment, and a single max_mem value
gleaned from the instance's flavor.  As such, it is not necessary to
invoke the expensive QueryReservedMemoryRequiredForPartition Job every
time we see a given max_mem value.

With this change set, the driver caches the instance overhead value
associated with each max_mem value it sees, making subsequent lookup
against that value effectively instantaneous.

The motivation for this change is scale.  It takes about one second for
QueryReservedMemoryRequiredForPartition to come back.  Since the
estimate_instance_overhead API is invoked via a periodic task, once per
second, serially across all instances, the driver begins to choke once
we reach about 80 instances on the host.

Change-Id: I5650b21b486658921b454a7ac0cd8ab745604b57
Closes-Bug: 1560668

commit_message:
Introduce component lead for fuel-ui

Now that fuel-ui has been separated into its own repository, we can get
get rid of the special case for it in our team structure, and elect a
component lead for fuel-ui in the Newton cycle. This separation also
allows us to go back to 1:1 matching between fuel-web the repository and
fuel-web the component.

Change-Id: I1346740c2ff9d41eb88af5312b8ddcffedbe5c8b

commit_message:
Add pagination helpers

In neutron core we want to deprecate
  neutron.db.sqlalchemyutils.paginate_query()
in favor of
  oslo_db.sqlalchemy.utils.paginate_query()

However, the oslo.db method takes different arguments. So we provide
helpers for converting the arguments to the oslo.db format.

Change-Id: I6de2945c7ed2ab48c285824a62ee0da61b030589

revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2016-03-09 09:45:55.000000000', 'files': ['api-ref/src/wadls/common_project.ent', 'api-ref/src/wadls/compute-api/src/v2.1/wadl/extensions-v2.1.wadl', 'api-ref/src/wadls/compute-api/src/v2.1/common.ent'], 'message': 'Compute extensions is lack of response parameters.

This patch adds missing parameters to Compute API v2.1 response
tables when users list/show extension(s):
 + updated: The last time update the extensions.
 + link: Links pertaining to this extension. This is a list of
 dictionaries, each including keys href and rel.
 + name: Name of the extension.

Compute extensions is lack of response parameters.

tables when users list/show extension(s):

 dictionaries, each including keys href and rel.

 + namespace: A URL pointing to the namespace for this extension.
 + alias: The alias for the extension.
 + description: The extension description.

commit_message:
Stops update_network handling updates it shouldn't

Currently update_network() attempts to update the network table with
any parameters that belong to a network, even if those attributes are
stored in a separate database table. This was causing certain update
commands to fail (such as updating dns_domain). The actual update to
dns_domain is handled by extensions called by the ml2 plugin, but this
function was also trying to process it and causing an error.

This patch ensures the network variable is only updated with
attributes that are actually in the networks table by filtering out
any parameters that don't match fields in the Network class model.

Change-Id: I54a736d91de52dda85c559b9e6103199f914abdf
Closes-bug: 1541560

commit_message:
WIP: Composable Details Views

This patch provides the ability for the registered detail views for
any resource type to be generically presented.  The term 'view' is
used specifically because the details should be composable, able to
be placed in a variety of contexts; for example, it could be
presented as a routable page, or as a modal.

This patch does the following:
 * Adds a Generic Detail display for routed pages
 * Adds a Modal Detail display service
 * Adds the concept of a Descriptor which contains a resource type name
   and an identifier.  The identifier can be something as simple as
   a string, but may also be an object (if the resource type needs more
   than one value to look up its data, e.g. Pool Members)
 * Adds the ability for a resource type to have knowledge about how one
   of its items may be loaded, so any detail page can fetch the information
   given a basic descriptor
 * Adds examples of how to use the descriptor on detail views so you
   don't have to constantly reload items via an API (just load base object
   once per detail view)
 * Removes the old custom page for Image and replaces the link from
   the table with a link to the Generic detail display.

Change-Id: I682979617829f1cfdb015945f819cacc6a3d6b51
Partially-Implements: blueprint angularize-images-table

Extensible details views in Angular

in Angular.  The premise is that each view you add presents a new tab to
the associated details view.

subject: Stop using rax for multinode
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-03-23 16:55:58.000000000', 'files': ['nodepool/nodepool.yaml'], 'message': "Stop using rax for multinode

Make this change until we have working eth0 and eth1 interfaces on rax
VMs as the multinode tests expect the private network to function if it
is present.

The underlying issue is that eth1 attempts to configure itself iwth dhcp
but there is no dhcp in rax and the glean config isn't in place before
eth1 is up'd. A new release of dib should fix this by removing the eth1
dhcp config and forcing glean to configure this interface.

Change-Id: I4daa46c56d701aedd99e10a69e7fa09b40dfaa47
"}]
commit_message:
Stop using rax for multinode

Make this change until we have working eth0 and eth1 interfaces on rax
VMs as the multinode tests expect the private network to function if it
is present.

The underlying issue is that eth1 attempts to configure itself iwth dhcp
but there is no dhcp in rax and the glean config isn't in place before
eth1 is up'd. A new release of dib should fix this by removing the eth1
dhcp config and forcing glean to configure this interface.

Change-Id: I4daa46c56d701aedd99e10a69e7fa09b40dfaa47

commit_message:
Add ansible fact clean up script to upgrade-utils

This change simply adds a fact cleanup script to the upgrade process
so that the system will gather fresh facts when upgrading. While this
will potentially add time to the upgrade process it will ensure we are
not running into issues from a previous release that may have been stored
in cached facts.

Change-Id: Ibae6e01d83ad4d53eafc63224c81e218de3ac013
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>

commit_message:
added api_db sync and made libvirtd-bin template configurable

* added sync for api_db (required in mitaka) and needed configuration options in
  nova.conf

  ubuntu (libvirtd needs to be started with just -l option on xenial)

commit_message:
Soft deletion for tasks

Instead of real deletion of tasks Nailgun now
mark it as deletion by recordring time deletion on
special datetime field `deleted_at`.

This changes required for spec below, because current
UI workflow required deletion in some of scenarios which
is conflict with idea of spec: save history of every
deployment tasks. So we save tasks using soft deletion
to show them using another API for tasks `/api/transactions`,
which will introduce in future patches.

Change-Id: I51a4b7c8871336ef14e79d229b3bccad7f6904aa
Implements: blueprint store-deployment-tasks-history

commit_message:
Improving config handling

This patch adds a validation step to the config class that can
be used to detect bad configs. For now it just asserts that if
legacy blacklist tests are mentioned the config contains the
required data block for them.

Additionally, this also removes various places in our test set
where a config file is specified. This was only done to satisfy
the old behaviour when a config was not optional.

Finally, this detects when a config has legacy data in it and
prints a deprecation warning.

Test coverage of the config class is now raised to 100%

Change-Id: I492a20f9b9f421d32e3e72eaa15f88c34c3d11e8

commit_message:
Elevate context for router lookups during floating IP association.

During a floating IP association, the tenant making the request
may not always be the owner of the router.  To make the association,
Neutron needs to query the router details internally but needs to
use an elevated context to do so.  Otherwise, the user sees a
cryptic error stating that the router doesn't exist.

Change-Id: If2bd6baa785ff879c61ce12e70b62e0ba25635f5
Closes-Bug: #1537754

commit_message:
Add floating ip to vertica master node

Vertica master node will be running vertica management
console, for end user to be able to use this console for
managing their clusters. By adding floating ip to the master
node we will be allowing users to access management console
from outside of the openstack environment/network

Implements: blueprint: floating-ip-on-vertica-master-node
Change-Id: I0ffb6ee3cf3032ba2e4d373c5f3b325bd2b24862

commit_message:
Fixes MySQL paths for RHEL and SUSE

This patchset aims to isolate the configuration paths from the guestagent
service implementation for the MySQL datastore and, that way, be able to
specify different configuration paths according to the underlying OS.

For that, there is a new file called sqlutil.py that has all configuration
information for the different OS's.

Also, considering we have configuration paths in the config.template for MySQL,
this patchset adds a way to re-render the configuration file to fit with the
platform.

Finally, it also fix the tests to reflect this new schema.

Change-Id: I4338ceaa90d5d1567c1333a23dd28ffaf8f7cbe7
Closes-Bug: #1450879

commit_message:
Enforce volume size on replica

Validates that the volume size on a replica is at least as
large as the master. This ensures the user doesn't attach
a slave that does not have enough space.

Closes-Bug: 1357500
Change-Id: I2bcdf440f935f13630d86e893c52e6325bc2efa7
